  {
    "source_type": "hackernews",
    "source_id": "d93f3ca6-53d8-4f6d-bed4-39d60bc13464",
    "title": "Show HN: YouTube MCP, give any AI agent access to YouTube",
    "description": "<p>I have a long YouTube watch-later playlist and wanted Claude to help me triage it by summarizing each video. It couldn't. I later discovered YouTube is not accessible to Claude, ChatGPT and majority of AIs. So I built this MCP server to fix that.<p>This is a local MCP server that gives any MCP-compatible client (Claude, ChatGPT, OpenClaw and others) 8 tools for working with YouTube content:<p>- fetch full transcript, with or without timestamps\n- download transcript as a .md file\n- get video metadata (title, channel, views, duration, likes, description)\n- search within captions for a keyword or phrase\n- download video or audio<p>No YouTube API key. No account. No signup. Everything runs locally on your machine against publicly available data.<p>Setup is one line:\nnpx @umbertotancorre/youtube-mcp<p>yt-dlp and ffmpeg are bundled automatically during install, so there's nothing to configure manually.<p>It's free and MIT licensed. Feedbacks are welcome.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48198790\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48198790</a></p>\n<p>Points: 5</p>\n<p># Comments: 3</p>",
    "url": "https://github.com/umbertotancorre/youtube-mcp",
    "published_at": "Tue, 19 May 2026 20:10:19 +0000",
    "fetched_at": "2026-05-22T10:48:36.052836+00:00"
  },
